<quantity id="4CA28EF4FFB7FFD07CD9F890F7F0DE2D" box="[690,763,1810,1836]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1082" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="in" value="8.3">8.3 in</quantity>
original description); fore wing, 
<number id="3D923136FFB7FFD07AFDF890F1C2DE2D" box="[1174,1225,1810,1836]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="12.9">12.9</number>
(
<quantity id="4CA28EF4FFB7FFD07AB5F890F03EDE2D" box="[1246,1333,1810,1836]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.667" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="in" value="10.5">10.5 in</quantity>
original description); hind wing, 
<number id="3D923136FFB7FFD07FA8F8B5F4E6DE50" box="[451,493,1847,1873]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.2">6.2</number>
. General coloration yellowish brown. Head yellowish brown shaded black on dorsum almost entirely, shaded heavier between ocelli. Antennae yellowish shaded gray on scape, black on pedicel, flagellum hyaline. Thorax orangeish brown shaded black mainly on pronotum. Pleura and sterna slightly paler shaded black on mesofurcasternal membrane and metasternum. Fore legs yellowish shaded with black except at articulations of segments and claws, pale; legs II‚ÄìIII whitish yellow shaded gray on femora and tibiae. Wings membrane hyaline translucent, veins brownish yellow, lighter toward apex. Abdomen yellowish completely shaded brownish gray except some pale markings, segment X slightly paler than the rest. Genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13613F94FFA8FFCF7F33FF5FF4FAD9F6" box="[344,497,221,247]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 ‚Äì 13" captionStartId="10.[151,270,1119,1143]" captionTargetBox="[169,1402,195,1092]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,175,1095]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 10 ‚Äì 13. Tortopus bellus: 10, male genitalia, v. v.; 11, details of apex of penes; 12, detail of pedestal, v. v.; 13, sockets on female abdominal sternum VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195433/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Figs. 
<number id="3D923136FFA8FFCF7FF4FF5FF4FAD9F6" box="[415,497,221,247]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10‚Äì12</number>
</figureCitation>
): sternum IX shaded with black on median 
<number id="3D923136FFA8FFCF7A64FF5FF110D9F6" box="[1039,1051,221,247]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3D923136FFA8FFCF7A43FF5FF132D9F6" box="[1064,1081,221,247]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="3.0">3</number>
, stronger on median furrow; pedestals and short parastyli (
<figureCitation id="13613F94FFA8FFCF7F9BFE82F74FD81B" box="[496,580,256,282]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 ‚Äì 13" captionStartId="10.[151,270,1119,1143]" captionTargetBox="[169,1402,195,1092]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,175,1095]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 10 ‚Äì 13. Tortopus bellus: 10, male genitalia, v. v.; 11, details of apex of penes; 12, detail of pedestal, v. v.; 13, sockets on female abdominal sternum VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195433/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Fig. 
<number id="3D923136FFA8FFCF7C4DFE82F74FD81B" box="[550,580,256,282]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) yellowish translucent; forceps whitish yellow shaded almost completely with black; penes translucent yellowish white, apex rounded (
<figureCitation id="13613F94FFA8FFCF7D01FEA0F6CBD83D" box="[874,960,290,316]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 ‚Äì 13" captionStartId="10.[151,270,1119,1143]" captionTargetBox="[169,1402,195,1092]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,175,1095]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 10 ‚Äì 13. Tortopus bellus: 10, male genitalia, v. v.; 11, details of apex of penes; 12, detail of pedestal, v. v.; 13, sockets on female abdominal sternum VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195433/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Fig. 
<number id="3D923136FFA8FFCF7DCAFEA0F6CBD83D" box="[929,960,290,316]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
